    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "THE OPPORTUNITY\n\nEma is looking for a high-velocity Product Marketing Manager to be the engine behind our product storytelling. You are a maker at heart—someone who can write a crisp blog post, coordinate a complex web launch, and work with designers to produce a cinematic demo video all in the same week.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - The Execution Engine: Own the \"last mile\" of our monthly product drops. You are the DRI ensuring everything from the webpage to the sales deck is live and flawless.\n\n - Cinematic Asset Production: Collaborate with our design team to create the most visually stunning product demos in the AI industry.\n\n - Case Study Factory: Partner with CSMs and PMs to find our best customer stories and turn them into interactive web experiences that prove the ROI of Ema.\n\n - Builder Advocacy: Work with the Builder Success team to translate technical updates into \"Why it Matters\" content for our developer community.\n\n - Sales Support: Be the rapid-response team for our AI Strategists, producing the collateral they need to win the market.\n\n\nWHO YOU ARE\n\n - 5+ Years in PMM or Product or GTM Strategy/Marketing: You have a portfolio of work (videos, pages, decks) that shows high \"marketing taste.\"\n\n - Proactive Maker: You don't wait for a brief. You start building, writing, and prototyping.\n\n - Technical \u0026 Curious: You want to understand how the \"Brain of Ema\" works so you can explain it better to the world.\n\n - Web-Savvy: You are comfortable working inside CMS tools and talking to developers to get content live.\n\n - Exceptional Writer: You can turn technical jargon into clear, compelling business value.\n\n - AI-Literate: You are already using tools like Lovable, Cursor, v0, or Claude to build and prototype.\n\nEma Unlimited is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, or genetics.",
